{{Infobox language |name=Mongphu |nativename= |states=China |ethnicity=[[Yi people|Yi]] |speakers=~500 |date=2015 |ref=<ref name="Hsiu2017">Hsiu, Andrew. 2017. [https://sites.google.com/site/msealangs/mondzish-branch/mongphu Mongphu audio word list]. Zenodo. http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1123361</ref> |familycolor=Sino-Tibetan |fam2=[[Lolo-Burmese languages|Lolo-Burmese]] |fam3=[[Mondzish languages|Mondzish]] |script= |iso3=none |glotto= |glottorefname= }} '''Mongphu''' or '''Mongpho''' (autonym: ''mɔŋ55 pʰɤ21'') is a [[Lolo-Burmese languages|Lolo-Burmese language]] of [[Yunnan]], China spoken in Lisa 里洒,<ref>[http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=258866 广南县八宝镇杨柳树村民委里洒自然村]</ref> [[Guangnan County]] and in Zhilun 值伦,<ref>[http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=206610 富宁县木央镇木兄坪村委会直伦一村小组]</ref><ref>[http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=206609 富宁县木央镇木兄坪村委会直伦二村小组]</ref> Upper Zhemei 上者梅,<ref>[http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=206600 富宁县木央镇木兄坪村委会上者梅村小组]</ref> Lower Zhemei 下者梅, and Muyang 木杨 villages of [[Funing County, Yunnan]]. There are several hundred speakers. It is likely most closely related to [[Maza language|Maza]] and [[Mango language|Mango]].
