'''Tsamai''' (also known as Ts'amay, S'amai, Tamaha, Tsamako, Tsamakko, Bago S'amakk-Ulo) is an [[Afro-Asiatic languages|Afro-Asiatic]] language spoken in [[Ethiopia]].<ref>Raymond G. Gordon Jr., ed.  2005.  ''Ethnologue:  Languages of the World''.  15th edition.  Dallas:  Summer Institute of Linguistics.</ref> Tsamai is a member of the [[Dullay languages|Dullay]] [[dialect continuum]]. Cule (Kuile, Kule) and evidently Dume (pseudo-pygmies) were apparently varieties.

